Class AbsSharedResultSet

  • java.lang.Object
    • ohos.data.resultset.AbsResultSet
      • ohos.data.resultset.AbsSharedResultSet
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ResultSet, SharedResultSet

    public abstract class AbsSharedResultSet
extends AbsResultSet
implements SharedResultSet
    Represents an abstract class that implements the SharedResultSet class.

    This class implements some basic functions of SharedResultSet.

    Since:
    3

      • fillBlock

        public void fillBlock​(int startRowIndex,
                      SharedBlock block)
        Description copied from interface: SharedResultSet
        Adds the data of a SharedResultSet to a SharedBlock.

        This method is used to add the data of a SharedResultSet (starting from the startRowIndex position) to a SharedBlock until all data of the SharedResultSet is added to the SharedBlock or the SharedBlock space is insufficient.

        Specified by:
        fillBlock in interface SharedResultSet
        Parameters:
        startRowIndex - Indicates the index in the SharedResultSet. The index starts from 0, indicating the first row.
        block - Indicates the block whose data is to be added to the SharedResultSet.
